# Core standards

- Prefer TypeScript with strict typing; avoid `any` unless justified.
- Keep functions small and single-purpose; avoid god modules.
- Don’t add dependencies without a clear reason and minimal surface area.
- Never log or return secrets (passwords, tokens, raw auth headers, cookies).
- When changing behavior, update or add tests or provide a reproducible test plan.
